triana.types

Interface SequenceInterface

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ComplexSampleSet, ComplexSpectrum, Curve, DefaultType, Document, EmptyingType, FileName, GraphType, Histogram, ImageMap, MailMsg, MatrixType, MultipleAudio, MultipleChannel, MultipleSpectra, Parameter, SampleSet, Spectrum, Spectrum2D, TimeFrequency, TrianaImage, TrianaPixelMap, TrianaType, VectorType

    public interface SequenceInterface
    Getter and Setter interface for the sequence number. All TrianaTypes can be part of an ordered sequence of data types.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description

    • Method Detail

      • getSequenceNumber

        int getSequenceNumber()
        Returns:
        the sequence number of this data type in the set. The default value of -1 infers that this data set is not part of a sequence.

      • setSequenceNumber

        void setSequenceNumber(int sequenceNumber)
        Parameters:
        sequenceNumber - the identifying number of this data type in the sequence.
